  "texts": [
    "In the aftermath of the miraculous event that saved the sailors' lives, Jonah remained consumed with anger and frustration.",
    "Despite witnessing the mercy and grace of God in action, he could not reconcile his own feelings towards the Ninevites.",
    "As Jonah resumed his journey to Nineveh, he couldn't help but shake his head in disbelief at the sight of the vast city.",
    "It was unlike any place he had ever been, and its wealth and extravagance left him feeling uneasy.",
    "During his walk, Jonah saw people of all shapes and sizes going about their daily lives."
